47 | |     Implements the standard interface for version number classes as
48 | |     described above.  A version number consists of two or three
49 | |     dot-separated numeric components, with an optional "pre-release" tag
50 | |     on the end.  The pre-release tag consists of the letter 'a' or 'b'
51 | |     followed by a number.  If the numeric components of two version
52 | |     numbers are equal, then one with a pre-release tag will always
53 | |     be deemed earlier (lesser) than one without.
54 | |
55 | |     The following are valid version numbers (shown in the order that
56 | |     would be obtained by sorting according to the supplied cmp function):
57 | |
58 | |         0.4       0.4.0  (these two are equivalent)
59 | |         0.4.1
60 | |         0.5a1
61 | |         0.5b3
62 | |         0.5
63 | |         0.9.6
64 | |         1.0
65 | |         1.0.4a3

67 | |         1.0.4
68 | |

70 | |

72 | |         2.7.2.2
73 | |         1.3.a4
74 | |         1.3pl1
